\begin_layout Section
Evaluation of arithmetic expression in C
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The operator precedence is as usual, i.e.
 1+2*3 are evaluated as 1 + (2*3).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The order for quotient and modulus are the same as multiplication and real
 division.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The operations are performed from left to right if they have the same precedence.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
However, please note that -1 * 2 is interpreted as "the product of negative
 one and 2".
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore, in this sense, the unary operator - (negative) and + (positive)
 is the fastest.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Note that, the exponent "e" , "E" is NOT an operator.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The computer interpret "1E+2" directly as the real number 
\begin_inset Formula $1\times10^{2}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
